$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Guhindura decimal kuri hexadecimal ninzira yoroshye, kandi irashobora gukorwa hamwe na calculatrice cyangwa guhinduranya kumurongo. Kugirango uhindure umubare, ugabanye na 16 hanyuma ufate ibisigaye. Ibisigaye noneho bizahuza numubare wuzuye. Kurugero, niba ufite umubare wimibare 234, gabanya na 16 hanyuma ufate ibisigaye: 234/16 = 14 R 2. Kubwibyo, mubisobanuro bitandatu, iyi mibare yandikwa nka &quot;E2&quot;.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Hano hari ibikoresho byinshi biboneka kumurongo bishobora gufasha muguhindura hagati yimibare icumi. Byongeye kandi, kubara byinshi bifite imikorere yubatswe izagufasha gukora iri hinduka byoroshye. Hamwe na kanda nkeya gusa yimbeba cyangwa kanda kuri clavier, urashobora guhindura agaciro kamwe kamwe muburyo bujyanye na hexadecimal ihwanye nayo!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Ni izihe nyungu zo gukoresha Hexadecimal kurenza Icumi?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'Hexadecimal, cyangwa base-16, sisitemu yashizweho kugirango yigane bimwe mubintu bimwe na sisitemu ya cumi. Muyandi magambo, yaremewe kugirango ibintu bitworoheye abantu. Umubare 423 ufite imibare 16 aho kuba imibare 10 iboneka muri sisitemu icumi. Ibi ni ukubera ko hexadecimal ikoresha ishingiro ryibimenyetso 16 aho kuba 10. Nyuma ya F, gahunda irongera itangirana na 0 nibindi nibindi kugeza tugeze kuri 15 byanditse nka F.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Kode ya Hexadecimal igabanya umubare wimibare kumunani iyo ugereranije na sisitemu ya cumi. Byongeye kandi, imibare itandatu ifite amakuru yubucucike bwikubye kabiri imibare icumi. None, ni ukubera iki ukwiye guhangayikishwa no kwiga iyi gahunda ishimishije yo kubara? Kuberako irashobora koroshya ubuzima bwawe! Mugihe ukorana na sisitemu ya sisitemu cyangwa ihererekanyamakuru, ukoresheje hex bizagutwara igihe n&#39;imbaraga mugihe ushushanya ubutumwa bwihishwa cyangwa amakuru yamakuru.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Ni izihe nyungu zo gukoresha Icumi hejuru ya Hexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Iyo bigeze kuri binary coding, Hexadecimal irakora neza kuko igabanya imibare 8 kugeza kuri 2. Byongeye kandi, Hex itanga urwego runini rwamakuru menshi kandi yukuri mumibare kuruta binary. Ibi biterwa nuko Hex ikoresha ibimenyetso 16 aho gukoresha bibiri gusa nka binary. Kubera ubwo buryo bwiyongereye, Hexadecimal ikoreshwa kenshi mugihe binary coding muri comptabilite na electronique ya digitale kimwe no mubumenyi bwa mudasobwa.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Mubyongeyeho, Hexadecimal ifata umwanya muto ugereranije na cumi. Hamwe n&#39;imibare ibiri gusa aho kuba imibare ibiri, imibare ya Hex igereranya umubare munini cyane. Ibi birashobora gufasha cyane mugihe ukorana na sisitemu ya mudasobwa, kuko hari amahirwe make yo kwibeshya mugihe wanditse kode ya hex ugereranije na code ya decimal ifite amanota menshi ya decimal ahantu hose!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Ni ubuhe bwoko bw&#39;indangagaciro zishobora kugaragazwa na Hexadecimal?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Umubare wuzuye ni umubare ukoresha imibare 16 aho gukoresha imibare 10 dukoresha muri sisitemu ya cumi. Iyi sisitemu yimibare yitwa base-16, kandi idufasha kwigana imiterere ya sisitemu icumi tumenyereye. Muri hexadecimal, buri mubare ugereranya imbaraga za 16. Imibare 0 kugeza 9 yerekana imbaraga za 1 kugeza 10, mugihe A kugeza F zerekana imbaraga za 11 kugeza 15.';
