$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Urashobora gukoresha ibice bitandatu kugirango uhindure hagati yimibare na binary. Kurugero, guhindura 10011011001010 muri hexadecimal byavamo 0x4F. Ibi bivuze ko agaciro 4F kagereranya numubare 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Mu mibare na siyanse ya mudasobwa, hexadecimal (nayo shingiro 16, cyangwa hex) ni sisitemu yimibare ihagaze hamwe na radix, cyangwa base, ya 16. Ikoresha ibimenyetso cumi na bitandatu bitandukanye, akenshi ibimenyetso 0-9 byerekana indangagaciro zeru kugeza icyenda, na A, B, C, D, E, F (cyangwa ubundi a - f) kugirango bahagararire agaciro icumi kugeza kuri cumi na gatanu. Kurugero, umubare wuzuye wa 2AF3 uringaniye, muri cumi, kugeza (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160), cyangwa 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Buri mibare itondekanya igereranya imibare ine (bits) (nanone yitwa &quot;nibble&quot;), kandi ikoreshwa ryibanze ryimyandikire ni nkumuntu-muntu ugereranya indangagaciro zibiri zanditse muri comptabilite na electronics. Kurugero, indangagaciro ya byte irashobora kuva kuri 0 kugeza kuri 255 (decimal) ariko irashobora kugaragazwa byoroshye nkimibare ibiri itondekanye mumirongo 00 kugeza kuri FF. Hexadecimal nayo ikoreshwa muburyo bwo kwerekana aderesi yibuka ya mudasobwa.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex ni impfunyapfunyo ya Hexadecimal, ishingiye ku shingiro -16 kandi ikoreshwa mu koroshya uburyo amabwiriza kuri mudasobwa ahagarariwe. Ibimenyetso 16 sisitemu sisitemu yateguwe nkuburyo bwo guhagarika umubare wa biti 8-biti, bityo amakuru ashobora kwinjizwa muri mudasobwa bitagoranye. Irashobora gucapurwa no kwandikwa ukoresheje imibare ibiri itandukanye ya hex hamwe na buri mubare wa hex yerekana nibble cyangwa wenda imiterere ya 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Sisitemu yimibare ikoresha ibimenyetso 16 byerekanwe murwego kuva 0-9 cyangwa AF. 0-9 byerekana imibare igera kuri icyenda mugihe AF ihagarariwe numubare 10-15. Ugereranije nubundi bwoko butatu bwimibare yimibare, sisitemu yimibare itandatu ifatwa nkuburyo bwiza cyane.';
